	<presentation id="products">
		<title short="API Products">API Products and API Product Management</title>
		<toc class="abstract">APIs are interfaces providing access to capabilities. As such, an API is just one way to make a capability accessible, but in today's increasingly digital world, they are of course a very important way. For the consumer, an API and the capability it represents are almost the same, and therefore it makes sense to talk about "API products" when referring not just to the technical API, but also to the capability that it represents. Managing API products is an important aspect of a successful API strategy and sustainable API management. As a starting point, it makes sense to consider the traditional "product marketing mix" and its 4 Ps, which are product, price, place, and promotion. The very same model can be applied to API products, only that they have a slightly different set of constraints than traditional products. We look at the key properties of API products, and how they influence the model of product, price, place, and promotion. We also look at how API product management helps to achieve the underlying goal of many API initiatives, which is to move IT from monolithic integrated models to a decentralized ecosystem.</toc>
